BANK OF AMERICA NATIONAL TRUST & SAVINGS ASS’N, etc., v. WESTERN WOMEN’S CLUB. No. 8699. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Jan. 7, 1937. See, also, 93 F.2d 189. Louis Ferrari and Geo. D. Schilling, both of San Francisco, Cal., for appellant. Byrne, Lamson & Jordan, of San Francisco, Cal., for appellee.

Before GARRECHT, MATHEWS, and HANEY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Pursuant to stipulation of counsel for respective parties, ordered appeal herein dismissed, that a decree of dismissal be filed and entered accordingly, and the mandate of this court issue forthwith.
